author: William A.
title: Military transport brings former President Obama’s things to Chicago for his library
text:
Military transport brings former President Obama’s things to Chicago for his library Posted at 10:47 pm on February 16, 2017 by William A. 
A report from Mary Ahern of NBC Chicago: Military Aircraft Delivers Obama Belongings to Chicago https://t.co/5oCJRChkJv 
— Mary Ann Ahern (@MaryAnnAhernNBC) February 17, 2017 Trending CNN survey says 'fake news' label isn't sticking, network's brand is as strong as ever 
NBC Chicago reports that a shipment of former President Barack Obama’s belongings arrived in Chicago Thursday morning via a military C-5 aircraft. 
A source exclusively told NBC 5 the artifacts will eventually end up in the Obama Presidential Center after spending some time in storage. The former president is expected to being a major fundraising effort for what will include the library, an event complex, and a museum. Here’s video of the moving project:
